Foods for your pre-workout breakfast:

•Banana - is the ideal food for those with little time before training;

•Tapioca - is a complex carbohydrate , of low absorption, so it is ideal to be consumed at least 1 hour before training, to give time to supply energy sources;

•Yogurt with dried fruits - they are simple and sugary carbohydrates, they are great options for replenish energy quickly.

Foods for your pre-workout coffee break:

•Fruit juice - lighter for pre-workout, fruit juice is a great option. They are practical and easy to digest, providing energy and stimulating muscle recovery;

•Whole grains - Another food group with a low glycemic index is whole grains. So, putting oatmeal in yogurt is always a good choice;

•Brown bread - Bread has been reviled a lot, but when you opt for whole-grain bread, you are promoting a series of benefits for your health.

Why do gym-goers have to drink plenty of water?

•Exercises at the gym cause sweating;

•Sweating leads to loss of water and electrolytes;

 •Adequate replacement of these losses is important for the functioning of the body.

•Drinking plenty of water maintains hydration during and after training.
